            <title>[JDK-8332904] ubsan ppc64le: c1_LIRGenerator_ppc.cpp:581:21: runtime error: signed integer overflow: 9223372036854775807 + 1 cannot be represented in type &apos;long int&apos;</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8332904</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>When using ubsan on Linux ppc64le we run into some overflows like this one&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
c1_LIRGenerator_ppc.cpp:581:21: runtime error: signed integer overflow: 9223372036854775807 + 1 cannot be represented in type &amp;#39;long int&amp;#39;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Seems we have to add casts to get defined behavior.&lt;br/&gt;
There are similar places in the coding as well.</description>
